  "uuid": "5d2eeb95a5e6a8c4697f40ec3e742f68",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<h3><u>Electrical Engineer (Retrofitting / A&A Works)</u></h3><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li><p>Supervise and coordinate electrical works for major retrofitting and A&A projects within an operational ICA building.</p></li><li><p>Review electrical drawings, technical submissions and method statements.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with consultants, contractors and other trades to ensure smooth site execution.</p></li><li><p>Oversee installation, testing and commissioning of electrical and ELV systems.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Singapore codes, safety regulations and project requirements.</p></li><li><p>Attend site meetings, inspections and support project handover documentation.<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>3–5 years’ relevant experience</strong>, preferably in <strong>retrofitting or A&A projects</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience working in <strong>live / operational buildings</strong> preferred.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Singapore electrical standards and WSH requirements.</p></li><li><p>Able to interpret electrical drawings and specifications.</p></li><li><p>Good coordination and communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Relevant certification (e.g. LEW) is an advantage.</p></li></ul>",
